  serving size: 359
---

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @orzo{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @asparagus{100%grams} and cut into thirds.

2 mins before the pasta has finished cooking, add the asparagus to the orzo and cook
until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain the pasta and asparagus in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan.
Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @double cream{150%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{15%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp}
and @water{75%ml} for the sauce into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @baby spinach{100%grams} to the pan a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @fresh pesto{32%grams}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}
and @butter{20%grams} (see pantry for amount) until the cheese and butter have melted.

Stir the cooked orzo and asparagus into the sauce until piping hot.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it
needs it.

Share the creamy pesto orzo between your #serving bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!